06850nam a22009015i 9781487582654DE-B159720210830012106.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210830t20191968onc    fo  d z      eng d  a97814875826547 a10.3138/97814875826542doi  a(DE-B1597)527995  a(OCoLC)1129177599  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aonccCA-ON 7aLCO0100002bisacsh00aOf Several Branches :bEssays from the Humanities Association Bulletin /ced. by Gerald McCaughey, Maurice Legris. 1aToronto : bUniversity of Toronto Press, c[2019] 4cÂ©1968  a1 online resource (284 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aHeritage00tFrontmatter -- tPreface -- tContents -- tIntroduction -- tPART I. Humanities in the Twentieth Century -- tThe Humanities in the Electronic Age -- tThe Catholic Church in the Mid-twentieth Century -- tTowards the Discovery of a New Quebec -- tSputnik and the Humanities -- tThe New Role of the Humanities in Canada -- tThe Humanities Association and the University -- tAn Ideal Programme for the Humanities -- tPART II. Approaches to Literary Tradition -- tComedy, Irony, and a Sense of Comprehension -- tNotes sur l'intuition comme instrument de critique creatrice -- tComment les Grecs concevaient la litterature -- tMill and Arnold: Liberty and Culture- Friends or Enemies? -- tHeber the Magnificent: Portrait of a Bibliophile -- tJacob Burckhardt and the "Ideal Past" -- tD' une litterature nationale -- tA Lack of Ghosts: Canadian Poets and Poetry -- tUn Continent litteraire a decouvrir -- tPART III. Writers and Their Works -- tTarquin, the Master-Mistress, and the Dark Lady: The Role of the Poet in Shakespeare's Sonnets -- tOiseaux, ou I' esthetique de Saint-John Perse -- tChaucer's "Retraction": Who Retracted What? -- tAn Approach to Wuthering Heights -- tStructure and Allegory in Tennyson's Idylls of the King -- tNarcissus Afloat -- tNotes on Contributors0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aOne of the most important functions of the Humanities Association of Canada is to bring together scholars from all disciplines of the humanities. Its boundaries thus extend considerably beyond literary studies. The annual meetings of the Association choose themes designed to demonstrate the relatedness of the humanities, based on a sense of professionalism beyond the narrow professionalism of a single discipline. This function is carried on for a larger audience by the Bulletin of the Association, in which these essays originally appeared. Drawn from issues covering the years 1954 to 1967, they discuss a broad range of topics from Chaucer to Saint-John Perse, from Greek literature to the electronic age. They include areas of Canadian literature both French and English, literary criticism, philosophy studies of the contemporary role of the humanities, a discussion of the "new Quebec." Among the distinguished contributors are A.S.P. Woodhouse, Claude Bissell, F.E.L. Priestley, John M. Robson, Marshall McLuhan, Wilfred Watson, Guy Sylvestre, and Giles Marcott.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Essays.2bisacsh1 aBissell, Claude T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrunet, Michel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCampbell, A.P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDozois, Camille, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuncan, A.R.C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLebel, Maurice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLegris, Maurice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLegris, Maurice, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.g